                <header class="post-header">
                    <h1 class="post-title-full">Building AI Agents at Scale</h1>
                    <p class="post-meta-full">
                        <time datetime="2025-01-15">January 15, 2025</time>
                    </p>
                </header>
                
                <div class="post-content">
                    <p>
                        As AI agents become more sophisticated, the challenges of building them at scale become increasingly apparent. 
                        At Notion, we've been exploring how to create agents that can handle complex workflows while maintaining reliability 
                        and user trust.
                    </p>

                    <h2>The Challenge</h2>
                    <p>
                        Building AI agents isn't just about training models—it's about creating systems that can integrate seamlessly with 
                        existing tools, understand context, and make decisions that align with user intent. The complexity multiplies when 
                        you're dealing with millions of users with diverse needs.
                    </p>

                    <h2>Key Insights</h2>
                    <p>
                        Through our work, we've learned that successful AI agents require:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Clear boundaries and well-defined capabilities</li>
                        <li>Robust error handling and graceful degradation</li>
                        <li>Transparent communication about what the agent is doing</li>
                        <li>Easy ways for users to provide feedback and correct mistakes</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h2>Looking Forward</h2>
                    <p>
                        The future of AI agents is incredibly exciting. As we continue to push the boundaries of what's possible, 
                        we're committed to building systems that augment human capabilities rather than replace them.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <footer class="post-footer">
